gomodel:SYNGO_2116  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: figure 6; CPG2 Knockdown Disrupts Constitutive Glutamate Receptor Internalization\n\nfigure 7; CPG2 Knockdown Disrupts Activity-Induced Internalization of AMPA Receptors. Experimental description: \"Embryonic medium-density hippocampal cultures were made as described (Brewer et al., 1993)\". This reference paper uses rats, and the cortical cultures were also made from rat;\n\n\"For postnatal high-density cortical cultures, cortices from P1 rats were plated onto poly-D-lysine and laminin-coated 6 cm dishes at 1.5 × 106 cells per dish in Neurobasal A medium (Invitrogen), supplemented with 0.5 mM L-glutamine and B27.\"\n\n\"Mouse monoclonal anti-CPG2 antibody 200A6.1 (IgG1) was generated against the peptide RKLESTLTGLEQSRERQERR (ResGen)\"\nWhich refers to sigma Anti-SYNE1 Antibody, clone 200A6, MABN857.\nWhich in turn links to uniprot ID Q63128 (supposed brain-specific splice variant of SYNE1)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-08-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2116" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

